1
00:01:40,520 --> 00:01:45,950
[THE DEVIL BETWEEN US]

2
00:01:45,970 --> 00:01:48,940
[Episode 3]

3
00:01:48,970 --> 00:01:54,110
[Nuanfeng Hengke]

4
00:01:54,140 --> 00:01:56,080
[Accounting Department]

5
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:00,840
Wu.

6
00:02:01,230 --> 00:02:02,310
Take a look at these for me.

7
00:02:02,310 --> 00:02:03,640
These are invoices from

8
00:02:03,920 --> 00:02:05,280
Public Relations Department.

9
00:02:05,280 --> 00:02:06,430
When were they booked?

10
00:02:06,430 --> 00:02:07,680
I don't remember.

11
00:02:18,240 --> 00:02:19,970
These guys spent a lot of money.

12
00:02:23,560 --> 00:02:24,680
Oh, I see.

13
00:02:24,990 --> 00:02:27,079
Mr. Sun instructed that

14
00:02:27,520 --> 00:02:29,310
these invoices don't comply with
the reimbursement regulations,

15
00:02:29,310 --> 00:02:31,430
but their work is special,

16
00:02:31,630 --> 00:02:33,320
so some costs can't be
claimed officially.

17
00:02:33,320 --> 00:02:34,320
Just let it go.

18
00:02:37,790 --> 00:02:40,990
We usually don't dig too deep into
public relations expenses.

19
00:02:40,990 --> 00:02:42,450
But these past few months,

20
00:02:42,550 --> 00:02:44,730
the amounts have been getting
higher and higher.

21
00:02:44,730 --> 00:02:46,730
If this keeps up,
it's bound to get us into trouble.

22
00:02:46,730 --> 00:02:47,740
What are you afraid of?

23
00:02:47,740 --> 00:02:50,540
Even if the sky falls,
the tall ones will hold it up.

24
00:02:51,110 --> 00:02:52,940
I’m just afraid the tall ones will duck,

25
00:02:52,940 --> 00:02:54,620
and we'll get flattened.

26
00:03:03,710 --> 00:03:04,610
Where are you going?

27
00:03:04,610 --> 00:03:06,040
I'll ask Mr. Sun for his opinion.

28
00:03:06,040 --> 00:03:07,150
See what we can do.

29
00:03:08,800 --> 00:03:09,430
Ken.

30
00:03:09,430 --> 00:03:09,960
Qiang.

31
00:03:09,980 --> 00:03:11,580
Help me check it quickly.

32
00:03:11,760 --> 00:03:13,890
Why haven't I got my salary this month?

33
00:03:16,710 --> 00:03:17,150
Qiang.

34
00:03:17,150 --> 00:03:18,590
Have a seat for a moment.

35
00:03:18,610 --> 00:03:19,840
I have to handle something.
We'll talk when I get back.

36
00:03:19,840 --> 00:03:20,420
No.

37
00:03:20,480 --> 00:03:21,530
I need the money urgently.

38
00:03:21,530 --> 00:03:23,390
Clear this up for me before you go.

39
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:27,660
Then I will tell you the truth.

40
00:03:28,360 --> 00:03:29,520
I think you know

41
00:03:29,840 --> 00:03:31,400
the reason clearly.

42
00:03:32,870 --> 00:03:35,470
You violated
the workshop equipment regulations

43
00:03:35,470 --> 00:03:37,740
and caused two production accidents.

44
00:03:38,160 --> 00:03:41,360
Your salary for this month
has been deducted completely.

45
00:03:41,390 --> 00:03:43,150
Since Hengke was established,

46
00:03:43,270 --> 00:03:44,360
I've been here.

47
00:03:45,410 --> 00:03:46,829
I've worked here for fifteen years.

48
00:03:46,829 --> 00:03:47,840
I'm a veteran here, right?

49
00:03:47,840 --> 00:03:48,440
Yes.

50
00:03:48,800 --> 00:03:50,730
Then how can you just
deduct my salary like that?

51
00:03:50,730 --> 00:03:51,610
Qiang.

52
00:03:52,070 --> 00:03:53,630
If you weren't a veteran,

53
00:03:53,800 --> 00:03:55,430
we would have

54
00:03:55,460 --> 00:03:56,750
let you pay for the damages.

55
00:03:56,750 --> 00:03:57,470
That's impossible.

56
00:03:57,470 --> 00:03:59,070
You're being unreasonable.

57
00:03:59,430 --> 00:04:01,190
I didn't break any rules.

58
00:04:01,290 --> 00:04:02,930
It was a machine failure.

59
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:03,950
I'm going to see Mr. Sun.

60
00:04:03,950 --> 00:04:04,820
Qiang.

61
00:04:05,190 --> 00:04:06,000
Calm down.

62
00:04:06,020 --> 00:04:07,410
You're retiring next year.

63
00:04:07,410 --> 00:04:08,440
You're not in the right here.

64
00:04:08,440 --> 00:04:10,440
Making a scene won't do you any good.

65
00:04:11,630 --> 00:04:12,520
I see.

66
00:04:13,560 --> 00:04:15,120
You're behind this,

67
00:04:15,240 --> 00:04:15,870
right?

68
00:04:16,360 --> 00:04:17,630
You just don't want to pay me, right?

69
00:04:17,630 --> 00:04:18,000
No.

70
00:04:18,019 --> 00:04:18,630
Am I right?

71
00:04:18,660 --> 00:04:19,769
I'm just an accountant.

72
00:04:19,769 --> 00:04:21,350
The money doesn't come out of my pocket.

73
00:04:21,350 --> 00:04:22,420
I have no reason to target you.

74
00:04:22,420 --> 00:04:24,000
Why are you explaining so much?

75
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:25,430
Leave now, or I'll call security.

76
00:04:25,430 --> 00:04:26,240
Stop it.

77
00:04:26,360 --> 00:04:26,800
Give me my money!

78
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:27,360
Qiang!

79
00:04:27,430 --> 00:04:28,270
Don't do anything rash, Qiang!

80
00:04:28,270 --> 00:04:29,240
I want my money!

81
00:04:29,240 --> 00:04:29,800
Help!

82
00:04:29,800 --> 00:04:30,430
Calm down.

83
00:04:30,430 --> 00:04:31,600
I want my money!

84
00:04:31,600 --> 00:04:32,000
Calm down!

85
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:32,750
Pay me my salary!

86
00:04:32,750 --> 00:04:34,310
Help! Call the police!

87
00:04:34,330 --> 00:04:34,950
Give me the money!

88
00:04:34,950 --> 00:04:35,560
Qiang.

89
00:04:35,870 --> 00:04:36,480
Qiang.

90
00:04:36,630 --> 00:04:37,630
I know you want money.

91
00:04:37,630 --> 00:04:39,270
Let's talk to Mr. Sun, okay?

92
00:04:39,310 --> 00:04:39,990
Don't move!

93
00:04:40,270 --> 00:04:41,530
Who dares come closer?

94
00:04:41,720 --> 00:04:42,750
I'll stab him if you do!

95
00:04:42,750 --> 00:04:43,190
Get back!

96
00:04:43,190 --> 00:04:44,000
Qiang!

97
00:04:44,090 --> 00:04:45,020
Back off!

98
00:04:45,120 --> 00:04:46,000
Qiang!

99
00:04:47,159 --> 00:04:47,800
Qiang!

100
00:04:48,210 --> 00:04:49,060
Back off!

101
00:04:49,510 --> 00:04:50,360
Don't be rash, Qiang!

102
00:04:50,360 --> 00:04:51,630
I'm walking.

103
00:04:51,950 --> 00:04:52,750
I didn't...

104
00:04:52,830 --> 00:04:53,390
Stay back!

105
00:04:53,390 --> 00:04:54,680
Think of your wife and kids!

106
00:04:54,680 --> 00:04:55,680
Qiang!

107
00:05:18,910 --> 00:05:19,480
Wang Ping.

108
00:05:19,480 --> 00:05:20,120
Wenjing,

109
00:05:20,230 --> 00:05:21,230
why are you here?

110
00:05:21,310 --> 00:05:22,160
What happened?

111
00:05:22,160 --> 00:05:23,130
We got a report.

112
00:05:23,230 --> 00:05:23,960
They said...

113
00:05:42,710 --> 00:05:43,909
Protect the scene.

114
00:05:56,970 --> 00:05:59,070
He walked me from
downstairs to the stairwell across.

115
00:05:59,070 --> 00:05:59,770
Just like this,

116
00:05:59,770 --> 00:06:00,910
we backed up the whole way.

117
00:06:00,910 --> 00:06:01,870
He had me by the neck

118
00:06:01,870 --> 00:06:03,390
and held scissors to my throat.

119
00:06:03,390 --> 00:06:04,000
Once we got here,

120
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:05,270
he didn't allow anyone to come over

121
00:06:05,270 --> 00:06:06,200
but stand there.

122
00:06:06,630 --> 00:06:07,720
When we got here,

123
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:09,000
he pushed me away.

124
00:06:09,480 --> 00:06:10,630
He muttered to himself,

125
00:06:10,630 --> 00:06:11,820
and then jumped.

126
00:06:12,390 --> 00:06:13,430
I didn't even touch him.

127
00:06:13,430 --> 00:06:14,680
I really didn't push him.

128
00:06:14,680 --> 00:06:15,700
He jumped on his own.

129
00:06:15,700 --> 00:06:17,030
Wu and the others saw it.

130
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:18,190
Yes.

131
00:06:18,210 --> 00:06:19,370
He jumped on his own.

132
00:06:19,800 --> 00:06:20,560
Before he jumped,

133
00:06:20,560 --> 00:06:22,160
what was he muttering about?

134
00:06:22,470 --> 00:06:23,830
He said something like,

135
00:06:24,800 --> 00:06:26,270
"I'm sorry to my wife and kids,"

136
00:06:26,270 --> 00:06:27,270
and "I can't go on living like this."

137
00:06:27,270 --> 00:06:28,400
He said these words.

138
00:06:29,570 --> 00:06:30,690
Do you guys know

139
00:06:30,980 --> 00:06:31,920
if he had any recent changes

140
00:06:31,920 --> 00:06:33,920
in his life or work?

141
00:06:34,950 --> 00:06:35,920
Changes?

142
00:06:35,920 --> 00:06:37,430
He made two mistakes at work this month.

143
00:06:37,430 --> 00:06:39,230
His entire salary was deducted.

144
00:06:39,240 --> 00:06:40,950
But one month's salary isn't much.

145
00:06:40,950 --> 00:06:42,550
It's not worth jumping over.

146
00:06:43,730 --> 00:06:44,320
Ken.

147
00:06:45,190 --> 00:06:46,620
Relax, don't be so nervous.

148
00:06:46,620 --> 00:06:47,680
There are so many witnesses here.

149
00:06:47,680 --> 00:06:49,040
You won't be wrongly accused.

150
00:06:49,040 --> 00:06:50,120
I want to relax

151
00:06:50,120 --> 00:06:50,430
but my...

152
00:06:50,430 --> 00:06:51,970
My legs are still jelly.

153
00:06:52,070 --> 00:06:53,040
It's okay. Don't be scared.

154
00:06:53,040 --> 00:06:54,190
I'm just asking routine questions.

155
00:06:54,190 --> 00:06:55,480
Think again.

156
00:06:55,530 --> 00:06:58,130
Was there anything abnormal
about him lately?

157
00:06:58,650 --> 00:06:59,710
Nothing abnormal.

158
00:06:59,760 --> 00:07:01,200
He's a gentle person.

159
00:07:01,710 --> 00:07:02,480
I don't know

160
00:07:02,480 --> 00:07:04,210
why he suddenly went mad today.

161
00:07:05,390 --> 00:07:06,560
I don't know if this counts.

162
00:07:06,560 --> 00:07:09,510
The moment he pushed me away just now,

163
00:07:09,720 --> 00:07:11,360
he whispered,

164
00:07:11,360 --> 00:07:12,600
"Sorry, Ken."

165
00:07:12,600 --> 00:07:14,190
He said it very calmly.

166
00:07:14,190 --> 00:07:14,770
Just one sentence?

167
00:07:14,770 --> 00:07:15,690
Yes.

168
00:07:15,920 --> 00:07:16,850
Write that down.

169
00:07:17,190 --> 00:07:18,450
Alright, we're done here.

170
00:07:18,450 --> 00:07:19,240
Who is the factory director?

171
00:07:19,240 --> 00:07:20,190
Anyway, if there's any news later,

172
00:07:20,190 --> 00:07:21,040
please contact us.

173
00:07:21,040 --> 00:07:21,510
Let's check the surveillance footage.

174
00:07:21,510 --> 00:07:22,510
I'm leaving, bro.

175
00:07:44,280 --> 00:07:44,950
Qiang.

176
00:07:45,750 --> 00:07:46,950
What happened to you?

177
00:07:47,750 --> 00:07:48,480
Master Liu.

178
00:07:50,159 --> 00:07:51,159
Liu Qiang

179
00:07:51,430 --> 00:07:53,430
is a veteran here.

180
00:07:53,590 --> 00:07:55,350
His work used to be fine.

181
00:07:55,680 --> 00:07:58,000
But this month,

182
00:07:58,920 --> 00:08:00,260
he made two basic mistakes,

183
00:08:00,260 --> 00:08:02,720
causing significant losses to the factory.

184
00:08:02,870 --> 00:08:04,480
Since our factory

185
00:08:04,830 --> 00:08:06,600
has always
had a people-oriented philosophy,

186
00:08:06,600 --> 00:08:08,270
and he's a veteran,

187
00:08:08,270 --> 00:08:10,210
we only symbolically docked his pay.

188
00:08:10,210 --> 00:08:11,940
We didn't punish him severely.

189
00:08:12,430 --> 00:08:14,030
We asked him to get a checkup,

190
00:08:14,070 --> 00:08:14,930
but he refused.

191
00:08:27,870 --> 00:08:29,260
Stop banging on the door.

192
00:08:29,260 --> 00:08:29,770
Stop banging!

193
00:08:29,770 --> 00:08:30,440
Quiet!

194
00:08:34,330 --> 00:08:35,270
I'm hungry.

195
00:08:35,270 --> 00:08:37,000
I know you're hungry. Sit down.

196
00:08:37,030 --> 00:08:37,320
Sit down.

197
00:08:37,320 --> 00:08:38,450
I bought groceries.

198
00:08:38,980 --> 00:08:40,309
We'll have dinner soon.

199
00:08:43,200 --> 00:08:43,870
Jiajia.

200
00:08:45,670 --> 00:08:46,320
Jiajia.

201
00:08:46,900 --> 00:08:47,690
Wake up.

202
00:08:48,030 --> 00:08:48,960
It's time to eat.

203
00:08:50,470 --> 00:08:51,840
Look at the time.
Why are you still sleeping?

204
00:08:51,840 --> 00:08:53,770
Aren't you going to sleep tonight?

205
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:56,150
Wake up.

206
00:08:59,910 --> 00:09:00,630
Jiajia.

207
00:09:03,840 --> 00:09:04,440
Jia.

208
00:09:06,790 --> 00:09:07,960
I'm calling you.

209
00:09:26,720 --> 00:09:27,600
I'm hungry.

210
00:09:27,630 --> 00:09:28,600
I know. Sit down.

211
00:09:28,620 --> 00:09:29,530
Sit down.

212
00:09:34,350 --> 00:09:36,080
Kidney function should be maintained

213
00:09:36,080 --> 00:09:38,610
to reduce the impact of uremia on
lung tissue.

214
00:09:39,900 --> 00:09:41,390
Let's get her admitted first.

215
00:09:41,390 --> 00:09:43,770
We'll use antibiotics
and nebulizer treatment

216
00:09:43,770 --> 00:09:45,590
to see if we can
get the condition under control.

217
00:09:45,590 --> 00:09:46,990
I'm counting on you, sir.

218
00:09:47,600 --> 00:09:48,510
Don't worry.

219
00:09:48,960 --> 00:09:50,440
Uremia complicated by lung infection

220
00:09:50,440 --> 00:09:52,300
is a fairly common complication.

221
00:09:52,550 --> 00:09:54,670
We have extensive experience treating it.

222
00:09:54,670 --> 00:09:56,870
Jiajia's condition isn't too serious.

223
00:10:02,750 --> 00:10:03,750
Go pay the fees.

224
00:10:05,270 --> 00:10:08,330
Director, there's something else
I'd like to discuss.

225
00:10:10,390 --> 00:10:13,270
She was supposed to
have the surgery last time.

226
00:10:13,600 --> 00:10:14,360
But since

227
00:10:14,360 --> 00:10:17,490
there was no kidney source,
she didn't have the surgery.

228
00:10:17,870 --> 00:10:18,710
Can the cost of

229
00:10:19,080 --> 00:10:21,410
hospitalization and treatment this time

230
00:10:21,510 --> 00:10:23,950
be deducted from
the surgery fee I prepaid?

231
00:10:24,270 --> 00:10:25,150
If it's not enough,

232
00:10:25,150 --> 00:10:26,080
I'll

233
00:10:26,100 --> 00:10:27,430
make up the difference.

234
00:10:28,200 --> 00:10:29,550
These are two separate things.

235
00:10:29,550 --> 00:10:31,720
The money you paid last time
has nothing to do with this.

236
00:10:31,720 --> 00:10:32,630
Okay. I see.

237
00:10:35,670 --> 00:10:36,600
How about this?

238
00:10:36,720 --> 00:10:39,030
Go apply for a refund of the surgery fee.

239
00:10:39,630 --> 00:10:42,110
The application takes a long time.

240
00:10:44,630 --> 00:10:45,510
I will tell you the truth.

241
00:10:45,510 --> 00:10:47,390
I don't have enough money now.

242
00:10:53,720 --> 00:10:55,000
Don't go to the billing counter.

243
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:56,150
Go straight to the Accounting Department.

244
00:10:56,150 --> 00:10:57,340
I'll call them

245
00:10:57,370 --> 00:10:59,420
and explain your situation in detail.

246
00:10:59,420 --> 00:11:00,650
They should be able to accommodate you.

247
00:11:00,650 --> 00:11:01,440
Okay, okay.

248
00:11:02,320 --> 00:11:03,230
Thank you, Director.

249
00:11:03,230 --> 00:11:03,760
Go ahead.

250
00:11:19,380 --> 00:11:20,260
69.

251
00:11:22,080 --> 00:11:23,360
Have you done these questions before?

252
00:11:23,360 --> 00:11:24,120
No.

253
00:11:24,640 --> 00:11:26,020
Then how did your score go up again?

254
00:11:26,020 --> 00:11:27,480
You didn't cheat, did you?

255
00:11:28,440 --> 00:11:29,870
It's a mock exam for
the postgraduate entrance examination.

256
00:11:29,870 --> 00:11:30,870
I did it for myself.

257
00:11:30,870 --> 00:11:32,600
Is there any point in cheating?

258
00:11:33,200 --> 00:11:34,750
I told you before that

259
00:11:34,750 --> 00:11:35,880
what really matters

260
00:11:36,010 --> 00:11:37,590
is finding the right method.

261
00:11:37,590 --> 00:11:39,230
I'm on the right track now,

262
00:11:39,360 --> 00:11:40,510
and I have endless energy.

263
00:11:40,510 --> 00:11:41,390
What method?

264
00:11:44,740 --> 00:11:45,670
I can't tell you.

265
00:11:46,340 --> 00:11:48,510
We're not even applying to
the same school.

266
00:11:48,510 --> 00:11:50,640
Do you really need to guard against me?

267
00:11:52,840 --> 00:11:54,360
I'm not guarding against you.

268
00:11:54,360 --> 00:11:57,090
I'm afraid you won't be able to
control yourself.

269
00:11:57,270 --> 00:11:58,200
What do you mean?

270
00:12:14,320 --> 00:12:15,780
I can only spare you three.

271
00:12:19,270 --> 00:12:20,200
What's this?

272
00:12:22,150 --> 00:12:24,320
I got these through a special channel.

273
00:12:25,120 --> 00:12:25,750
To be honest,

274
00:12:25,750 --> 00:12:27,630
they contain stimulants.

275
00:12:28,590 --> 00:12:29,890
But you must control the dosage

276
00:12:29,890 --> 00:12:31,070
because it's addictive.

277
00:12:31,070 --> 00:12:32,740
Take at most one a day.

278
00:12:34,580 --> 00:12:35,660
Stimulants?

279
00:12:39,120 --> 00:12:41,180
Give them back if you don't want them.

280
00:12:43,550 --> 00:12:44,200
We're classmates.

281
00:12:44,200 --> 00:12:45,530
I don't want to harm you.

282
00:12:46,060 --> 00:12:47,590
Taking too many isn't good.

283
00:12:47,750 --> 00:12:48,910
Once your scores improve,

284
00:12:48,910 --> 00:12:50,310
after two months at most,

285
00:12:50,390 --> 00:12:51,510
you must quit.

286
00:12:53,670 --> 00:12:54,670
And only those with

287
00:12:54,670 --> 00:12:55,840
very strong willpower

288
00:12:55,840 --> 00:12:56,790
can quit.

289
00:13:07,760 --> 00:13:10,090
I've been taking the postgraduate exam
for three years.

290
00:13:10,090 --> 00:13:12,130
I kept trying despite repeated failures.

291
00:13:12,130 --> 00:13:14,130
Who has stronger willpower than me?

292
00:13:18,310 --> 00:13:20,510
Isn't this just ordinary coffee candy?

293
00:13:20,570 --> 00:13:21,770
Keep it in your mouth.

294
00:13:22,660 --> 00:13:25,120
Wait until it melts,
and you'll understand.

295
00:13:26,980 --> 00:13:27,720
Three for 300 yuan.

296
00:13:27,720 --> 00:13:28,630
Pay me.

297
00:13:30,070 --> 00:13:31,080
I have to pay?

298
00:13:32,520 --> 00:13:33,430
Duh.

299
00:13:36,360 --> 00:13:37,420
Give me a discount?

300
00:13:39,320 --> 00:13:40,240
One pill a day.

301
00:13:40,600 --> 00:13:41,480
You'll spend 3,000 yuan a month,

302
00:13:41,480 --> 00:13:42,680
and only 6,000 yuan for two months.

303
00:13:42,680 --> 00:13:44,150
It can help you
get into your dream college.

304
00:13:44,150 --> 00:13:45,210
Is that expensive?

305
00:14:29,200 --> 00:14:29,960
You're back.

306
00:14:32,420 --> 00:14:33,220
Yes.

307
00:14:36,480 --> 00:14:38,010
What are you smiling about?

308
00:14:39,400 --> 00:14:40,420
Dinner is ready.

309
00:15:00,480 --> 00:15:02,320
When we were messaging today,

310
00:15:02,390 --> 00:15:04,000
an old colleague at my company...

311
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:06,200
I've been studying really well lately.

312
00:15:06,510 --> 00:15:08,710
I'll definitely get an offer next year.

313
00:15:13,660 --> 00:15:14,450
Really?

314
00:15:16,120 --> 00:15:18,790
I've never seen you this confident.

315
00:15:22,050 --> 00:15:22,810
By the way,

316
00:15:23,030 --> 00:15:24,400
what were you saying just now?

317
00:15:24,400 --> 00:15:26,130
What happened at your company?

318
00:15:26,630 --> 00:15:27,710
Nothing.

319
00:15:29,200 --> 00:15:31,790
As long as we get over
this hurdle smoothly,

320
00:15:32,910 --> 00:15:34,240
life for the two of us

321
00:15:34,240 --> 00:15:35,710
will definitely get better and better,

322
00:15:35,710 --> 00:15:36,230
right?

323
00:15:40,480 --> 00:15:41,240
Stop grinning like an idiot.

324
00:15:41,240 --> 00:15:42,170
Wash your hands.

325
00:15:54,790 --> 00:15:55,430
Sis.

326
00:15:57,510 --> 00:15:58,840
Thanks for everything.

327
00:16:46,760 --> 00:16:48,160
How much is this milk tea?

328
00:16:49,200 --> 00:16:49,960
260 yuan.

329
00:16:51,040 --> 00:16:52,240
What about the candy?

330
00:16:53,770 --> 00:16:54,630
50 yuan a piece.

331
00:16:57,400 --> 00:16:58,420
What a rip-off.

332
00:17:02,470 --> 00:17:03,730
How many grams of drugs

333
00:17:03,840 --> 00:17:05,170
are there in this candy?

334
00:17:05,589 --> 00:17:06,880
About 100 micrograms.

335
00:17:09,420 --> 00:17:11,220
One gram sells for 500,000 yuan.

336
00:17:12,800 --> 00:17:14,460
What's the raw material cost?

337
00:17:16,030 --> 00:17:17,190
Over 3,300 yuan.

338
00:17:25,849 --> 00:17:27,250
That day at Black Forest,

339
00:17:27,670 --> 00:17:28,870
how many did you want?

340
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:30,000
450 grams.

341
00:17:30,310 --> 00:17:31,310
450 grams.

342
00:17:33,680 --> 00:17:35,340
That's over 100 million yuan.

343
00:17:36,720 --> 00:17:38,480
What good is all that money?

344
00:17:38,850 --> 00:17:40,220
The contact got caught.

345
00:17:40,920 --> 00:17:42,850
The police must have got the goods.

346
00:17:45,310 --> 00:17:47,040
I followed Hu Wenjing that day.

347
00:17:47,640 --> 00:17:48,970
I heard their words that

348
00:17:49,870 --> 00:17:51,190
the suspect died

349
00:17:52,160 --> 00:17:53,760
but the drugs weren't found.

350
00:17:55,550 --> 00:17:56,310
Why didn't you tell me

351
00:17:56,310 --> 00:17:57,790
this important information?

352
00:17:57,790 --> 00:17:58,920
You didn't ask.

353
00:18:25,830 --> 00:18:26,780
Forget it.

354
00:18:27,720 --> 00:18:29,520
If the police can't even find it,

355
00:18:30,310 --> 00:18:31,570
how are we supposed to?

356
00:18:33,790 --> 00:18:34,960
I used a backup account

357
00:18:34,960 --> 00:18:36,480
to buy some things online.

358
00:18:38,430 --> 00:18:40,320
The address and phone number are fake.

359
00:18:40,320 --> 00:18:41,440
It hasn't arrived yet.

360
00:18:41,440 --> 00:18:42,440
When it arrives,

361
00:18:42,680 --> 00:18:43,820
go pick it up for me.

362
00:18:44,270 --> 00:18:46,470
I need to see Daquan as soon as possible.

363
00:18:47,940 --> 00:18:49,250
Can I try this?

364
00:18:51,680 --> 00:18:52,360
Sure.

365
00:19:00,270 --> 00:19:01,270
Any side effects?

366
00:19:01,400 --> 00:19:02,240
You'll die.

367
00:19:07,750 --> 00:19:08,810
You must be joking.

368
00:19:09,180 --> 00:19:10,780
So many people have drunk it.

369
00:19:10,860 --> 00:19:12,250
Are they all dead?

370
00:19:12,920 --> 00:19:15,320
Not if you don't overdose
in the short term.

371
00:19:15,350 --> 00:19:17,480
But this hallucinogen is terrifying.

372
00:19:17,790 --> 00:19:19,360
Different people

373
00:19:19,550 --> 00:19:21,080
have different reactions.

374
00:19:25,240 --> 00:19:28,310
At first, it brings
euphoria and confidence,

375
00:19:28,380 --> 00:19:29,840
and even hallucinations.

376
00:19:35,300 --> 00:19:36,560
Once you're addicted,

377
00:19:36,880 --> 00:19:38,160
you'll suffer insomnia,

378
00:19:38,160 --> 00:19:38,830
anorexia,

379
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:39,930
and weight loss.

380
00:19:40,440 --> 00:19:42,400
It will make you lose your judgment,

381
00:19:42,400 --> 00:19:43,880
change your brain structure,

382
00:19:43,880 --> 00:19:45,310
distort your perception,

383
00:19:45,310 --> 00:19:46,770
and ruin your personality

384
00:19:47,000 --> 00:19:48,510
until you truly believe that

385
00:19:48,510 --> 00:19:49,720
it's a good thing

386
00:19:49,740 --> 00:19:50,940
and can never quit it.

387
00:19:51,590 --> 00:19:52,550
In the end,

388
00:19:54,390 --> 00:19:55,700
you'll suffocate,

389
00:19:56,170 --> 00:19:56,850
go mad,

390
00:19:57,220 --> 00:19:58,280
become depressed,

391
00:19:58,830 --> 00:20:00,230
and have cardiac arrest.

392
00:20:08,030 --> 00:20:08,960
Anyway,

393
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:11,480
I never take it.

394
00:20:13,160 --> 00:20:14,830
If you don't believe me,

395
00:20:15,900 --> 00:20:16,900
you can try it.

396
00:20:35,830 --> 00:20:37,620
Liu Qiang committed suicide?

397
00:20:38,400 --> 00:20:39,030
What...

398
00:20:40,190 --> 00:20:41,990
How is that possible?

399
00:20:44,420 --> 00:20:44,960
Look at the time.

400
00:20:44,960 --> 00:20:45,880
Why are you still making noise?

401
00:20:45,880 --> 00:20:46,750
Go to bed, now.

402
00:20:51,860 --> 00:20:53,520
Liu Qiang committed suicide?

403
00:20:54,750 --> 00:20:55,590
Is that true?

404
00:20:55,590 --> 00:20:56,550
Yes.

405
00:20:56,950 --> 00:20:58,500
When was the last time you saw him?

406
00:20:58,500 --> 00:20:58,870
I...

407
00:20:59,150 --> 00:21:00,800
I texted him a couple of days ago

408
00:21:00,800 --> 00:21:02,200
about your blind date with his nephew.

409
00:21:02,200 --> 00:21:03,680
I mean meeting in person.

410
00:21:04,110 --> 00:21:04,880
Meeting him?

411
00:21:05,800 --> 00:21:07,730
I haven't seen him for over a month.

412
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:09,640
When you last met him,

413
00:21:09,640 --> 00:21:11,570
did you notice anything abnormal?

414
00:21:12,720 --> 00:21:14,550
Nothing abnormal.

415
00:21:16,480 --> 00:21:17,000
Before,

416
00:21:17,000 --> 00:21:20,030
I used to ask him to go to
the foot massage parlor.

417
00:21:20,170 --> 00:21:21,160
But the last few times I asked,

418
00:21:21,160 --> 00:21:22,220
he didn't come out.

419
00:21:25,590 --> 00:21:27,000
When you last saw him,

420
00:21:27,020 --> 00:21:27,540
did you

421
00:21:27,790 --> 00:21:29,240
notice any injuries on him,

422
00:21:29,240 --> 00:21:30,830
or maybe needle marks?

423
00:21:31,310 --> 00:21:33,150
You didn't pay attention to that, right?

424
00:21:33,150 --> 00:21:34,200
I didn't pay attention to that.

425
00:21:34,200 --> 00:21:36,160
I think there weren't any injuries.

426
00:21:36,160 --> 00:21:37,220
Are your questions

427
00:21:37,440 --> 00:21:38,880
related to Liu Qiang's death?

428
00:21:38,880 --> 00:21:39,480
No, just curious.

429
00:21:39,480 --> 00:21:40,400
I remembered you knew him,

430
00:21:40,400 --> 00:21:41,600
so I'm just checking.

431
00:21:42,160 --> 00:21:42,920
My god.

432
00:21:44,670 --> 00:21:45,540
By the way, Dad.

433
00:21:45,840 --> 00:21:47,350
It's not safe around here lately.

434
00:21:47,350 --> 00:21:49,240
Don't eat anything when you're out.

435
00:21:49,240 --> 00:21:50,590
If you need food or drinks,

436
00:21:50,590 --> 00:21:51,960
go to big supermarkets.

437
00:21:51,960 --> 00:21:54,830
If you're really not sure,
bring it back for me to check.

438
00:21:54,830 --> 00:21:56,640
I can protect you now.

439
00:21:56,640 --> 00:21:58,720
If anything happens, you must tell me.

440
00:21:58,720 --> 00:21:59,480
Don't worry.

441
00:21:59,480 --> 00:22:01,030
I know

442
00:22:01,350 --> 00:22:01,980
what I shouldn't do.

443
00:22:01,980 --> 00:22:02,780
That's right.

444
00:22:04,020 --> 00:22:05,150
Don't leave.

445
00:22:06,310 --> 00:22:07,480
You have to remember that

446
00:22:07,480 --> 00:22:09,530
you have parents and kids

447
00:22:09,550 --> 00:22:10,630
who are all waiting for you to come back.

448
00:22:10,630 --> 00:22:11,150
I know.

449
00:22:11,170 --> 00:22:13,650
Know your limits on your missions.

450
00:22:13,680 --> 00:22:15,030
Don't push yourself so hard.

451
00:22:15,030 --> 00:22:16,640
Whether you catch the criminal or not

452
00:22:16,640 --> 00:22:18,590
isn't that important to us.

453
00:22:18,610 --> 00:22:19,710
If you don't catch criminals this time,

454
00:22:19,710 --> 00:22:21,640
you'll have the chance next time.

455
00:22:21,790 --> 00:22:23,550
But do you know what matters most?

456
00:22:23,550 --> 00:22:25,880
We all want you to come home safe,

457
00:22:25,880 --> 00:22:26,790
my girl.

458
00:22:26,790 --> 00:22:27,350
I see.

459
00:22:27,350 --> 00:22:28,400
I know what I'm doing.

460
00:22:28,400 --> 00:22:29,240
Don't worry.

461
00:22:29,240 --> 00:22:30,400
Finish washing up and go to sleep.

462
00:22:30,400 --> 00:22:31,400
Remember that.

463
00:22:31,400 --> 00:22:32,220
Okay.

464
00:22:53,350 --> 00:22:54,780
I'm going for a smoke.

465
00:23:00,220 --> 00:23:01,220
Going for a smoke?

466
00:23:01,990 --> 00:23:03,270
Not allowed in the ward.

467
00:23:03,270 --> 00:23:04,200
In the corridor?

468
00:23:05,070 --> 00:23:05,510
Okay.

469
00:23:08,360 --> 00:23:09,030
Ma'am?

470
00:23:09,180 --> 00:23:09,900
Ma'am?

471
00:23:10,200 --> 00:23:11,190
Please help keep an eye on my child
for a while.

472
00:23:11,190 --> 00:23:12,300
Okay. Go ahead.

473
00:23:15,790 --> 00:23:16,880
Hungry.

474
00:23:17,440 --> 00:23:18,920
Xiaoyu is hungry.

475
00:23:19,400 --> 00:23:21,120
I want to eat.

476
00:23:23,340 --> 00:23:24,780
I'm hungry.

477
00:23:24,810 --> 00:23:27,570
One, two, three, four, five.

478
00:23:27,640 --> 00:23:28,270
Five!

479
00:23:28,440 --> 00:23:29,070
Five!

480
00:23:29,070 --> 00:23:30,980
I counted to five!

481
00:23:42,880 --> 00:23:43,710
Jiajia.

482
00:23:45,410 --> 00:23:46,640
I've been watching you two for a while.

483
00:23:46,640 --> 00:23:48,390
Smoking isn't allowed in the hospital.

484
00:23:48,390 --> 00:23:49,150
Okay.

485
00:23:54,310 --> 00:23:55,480
Actually, I quit smoking years ago.

486
00:23:55,480 --> 00:23:56,320
Okay.

487
00:24:05,290 --> 00:24:06,450
How old is your son?

488
00:24:07,490 --> 00:24:08,580
Not yet ten.

489
00:24:09,100 --> 00:24:09,790
How old is your daughter?

490
00:24:09,790 --> 00:24:10,550
About the same.

491
00:24:10,550 --> 00:24:11,210
She's nine.

492
00:24:12,530 --> 00:24:13,590
What does she have?

493
00:24:14,160 --> 00:24:15,030
Uremia

494
00:24:16,720 --> 00:24:18,580
with a secondary lung infection.

495
00:24:19,070 --> 00:24:21,590
Once the pneumonia is cured,

496
00:24:21,590 --> 00:24:24,160
she just needs a kidney transplant
for the uremia, right?

497
00:24:24,160 --> 00:24:24,800
Yes.

498
00:24:25,440 --> 00:24:26,240
But

499
00:24:26,920 --> 00:24:27,680
we need a donor kidney.

500
00:24:27,680 --> 00:24:29,740
We're currently waiting for a match.

501
00:24:30,270 --> 00:24:31,990
Why don't you and your wife have a try?

502
00:24:31,990 --> 00:24:35,050
Direct relatives are usually good matches.

503
00:24:35,170 --> 00:24:36,370
My wife passed away.

504
00:24:39,070 --> 00:24:41,790
I have chronic glomerulonephritis.

505
00:24:42,900 --> 00:24:45,300
I'll end up with uremia
sooner or later too.

506
00:24:50,790 --> 00:24:51,680
What about your son?

507
00:24:51,680 --> 00:24:53,240
What does he have?

508
00:24:55,830 --> 00:24:57,360
Congenital heart disease.

509
00:24:58,640 --> 00:25:00,070
He caught a cold a couple of days ago,

510
00:25:00,070 --> 00:25:01,730
and we had to rush him to the ER.

511
00:25:02,830 --> 00:25:04,110
Will surgery work?

512
00:25:04,960 --> 00:25:07,170
The doctor said the cold caused

513
00:25:07,200 --> 00:25:09,200
a severe lung infection.

514
00:25:09,640 --> 00:25:12,470
He's not strong enough
for surgery right now.

515
00:25:14,680 --> 00:25:16,230
They implied a few days ago

516
00:25:16,230 --> 00:25:18,310
that my son

517
00:25:18,440 --> 00:25:19,600
might die this time.

518
00:25:24,480 --> 00:25:25,740
He'll recover slowly.

519
00:25:26,030 --> 00:25:26,680
Yeah.

520
00:25:30,060 --> 00:25:31,690
I probably shouldn't say this,

521
00:25:31,690 --> 00:25:33,720
but sometimes I think

522
00:25:35,000 --> 00:25:37,260
it might be better if he just passed away,

523
00:25:37,730 --> 00:25:39,330
which can end his suffering.

524
00:25:40,720 --> 00:25:43,040
Treating him these past two years

525
00:25:43,640 --> 00:25:45,400
has wiped out our savings

526
00:25:45,400 --> 00:25:46,730
and left us deep in debt.

527
00:25:48,440 --> 00:25:49,310
They say there are no filial sons

528
00:25:49,310 --> 00:25:51,370
at the bedside of the long-term sick.

529
00:25:59,200 --> 00:26:01,030
Look at these two kids.

530
00:26:02,000 --> 00:26:03,530
Both have lung infections.

531
00:26:04,000 --> 00:26:05,400
Both are complications.

532
00:26:05,530 --> 00:26:06,440
And they're in the same ward.

533
00:26:06,440 --> 00:26:07,070
It's fate.

534
00:26:07,200 --> 00:26:07,720
Yes.

535
00:26:09,720 --> 00:26:11,350
If anything happens,

536
00:26:11,640 --> 00:26:12,480
let's look out for each other.

537
00:26:12,480 --> 00:26:13,310
Definitely.

538
00:26:16,070 --> 00:26:16,960
Hello.

539
00:26:18,240 --> 00:26:19,190
Is that Cheng Ken?

540
00:26:19,190 --> 00:26:19,710
Yes.

541
00:26:20,240 --> 00:26:22,370
I'm from the Neighborhood Committee.

542
00:26:22,980 --> 00:26:25,070
Someone's been screaming
in your apartment.

543
00:26:25,070 --> 00:26:27,000
Is a child trapped in the bathroom?

544
00:26:27,070 --> 00:26:28,330
We are going to pry the door open.

545
00:26:28,330 --> 00:26:29,180
No, no, no.

546
00:26:29,270 --> 00:26:29,880
Don't pry it open.

547
00:26:29,880 --> 00:26:30,550
That's my family.

548
00:26:30,550 --> 00:26:31,200
Don't freak her out.

549
00:26:31,200 --> 00:26:32,240
I'll be right back.

550
00:26:32,240 --> 00:26:34,080
Bro, please keep an eye on
the child for me.

551
00:26:34,080 --> 00:26:35,270
I have an emergency at home.

552
00:26:35,270 --> 00:26:36,220
Okay, okay.

553
00:26:39,990 --> 00:26:40,720
Don't worry.

554
00:26:40,830 --> 00:26:41,310
Okay.

555
00:26:57,340 --> 00:26:58,000
Letting her out.

556
00:26:58,000 --> 00:26:59,080
It's troublesome.

557
00:26:59,340 --> 00:26:59,970
Mrs. Wang,

558
00:27:00,190 --> 00:27:01,270
Mrs. Zhang, I'm sorry.

559
00:27:01,270 --> 00:27:01,680
Sorry.

560
00:27:01,680 --> 00:27:02,200
Sorry for coming back late.

561
00:27:02,200 --> 00:27:02,960
Cheng Ken.

562
00:27:03,160 --> 00:27:05,890
Why is there a mental patient
living in your house?

563
00:27:05,890 --> 00:27:07,370
It's my niece.

564
00:27:07,720 --> 00:27:09,090
She just moved here.

565
00:27:09,110 --> 00:27:10,310
I have to take care of her for a while.

566
00:27:10,310 --> 00:27:10,960
Sorry.

567
00:27:10,960 --> 00:27:12,400
Will

568
00:27:12,400 --> 00:27:13,590
she come out and hurt others?

569
00:27:13,590 --> 00:27:14,070
No, she won't.

570
00:27:14,070 --> 00:27:15,310
She is young.

571
00:27:15,310 --> 00:27:16,440
Only fifteen years old.

572
00:27:16,440 --> 00:27:17,270
She's usually quiet.

573
00:27:17,270 --> 00:27:18,070
I always kept a close watch on her.

574
00:27:18,070 --> 00:27:18,880
I don't know what happened today.

575
00:27:18,880 --> 00:27:20,310
I took Jiajia to the hospital just now.

576
00:27:20,310 --> 00:27:21,030
It was urgent.

577
00:27:21,030 --> 00:27:21,750
She might be hungry.

578
00:27:21,750 --> 00:27:22,350
Sorry.

579
00:27:22,420 --> 00:27:22,720
Sorry.

580
00:27:22,720 --> 00:27:23,800
It won't happen again.

581
00:27:23,800 --> 00:27:24,680
Sorry for the disturbance.

582
00:27:24,680 --> 00:27:25,640
Please go home.

583
00:27:26,510 --> 00:27:27,510
Okay. Let's go.

584
00:27:27,530 --> 00:27:28,620
Sorry.

585
00:27:35,790 --> 00:27:36,940
Stop knocking.

586
00:27:38,820 --> 00:27:39,680
Stop knocking.

587
00:27:43,070 --> 00:27:44,200
What are you screaming for?

588
00:27:44,200 --> 00:27:45,160
Why are you screaming?

589
00:27:45,160 --> 00:27:47,200
I'm hungry.

590
00:27:47,200 --> 00:27:48,030
Stop screaming.

591
00:27:48,030 --> 00:27:48,480
Shut up!

592
00:27:48,480 --> 00:27:50,610
Scream again, and you will get no food!

593
00:27:51,110 --> 00:27:54,370
I want meat.

594
00:27:54,830 --> 00:27:57,180
I want meat.

595
00:28:03,240 --> 00:28:04,200
Eat this first.

596
00:28:04,200 --> 00:28:05,070
It's yummy.

597
00:28:05,240 --> 00:28:05,750
Sit.

598
00:28:05,750 --> 00:28:06,640
Sit down.

599
00:28:06,640 --> 00:28:08,200
Sit down.

600
00:28:10,920 --> 00:28:12,180
I'll get you some meat.

601
00:28:44,680 --> 00:28:45,550
Do you like it?

602
00:28:47,490 --> 00:28:48,250
Is it good?

603
00:29:26,780 --> 00:29:27,830
You're back.

604
00:29:31,460 --> 00:29:32,060
How is she?

605
00:29:32,110 --> 00:29:33,240
Everything's fine.

606
00:29:35,310 --> 00:29:37,960
Dr. Yang came by earlier.

607
00:29:38,720 --> 00:29:39,720
He's my classmate.

608
00:29:39,720 --> 00:29:40,880
He works here.

609
00:29:41,110 --> 00:29:43,110
It's good to know people in the hospital.

610
00:29:43,110 --> 00:29:44,260
Dr. Yang said

611
00:29:44,790 --> 00:29:46,400
he had checked on Jiajia.

612
00:29:46,440 --> 00:29:47,550
Her fever has gone down.

613
00:29:47,550 --> 00:29:48,920
She's fine. Don't worry.

614
00:29:48,920 --> 00:29:49,590
Okay.

615
00:29:50,350 --> 00:29:50,880
Thank you.

616
00:29:50,880 --> 00:29:51,790
No problem.

617
00:29:53,350 --> 00:29:54,610
What should I call you?

618
00:29:55,400 --> 00:29:56,530
My surname is Cheng.

619
00:29:58,200 --> 00:29:58,920
Cheng Ken.

620
00:29:59,070 --> 00:30:00,670
Cheng means a bright future.

621
00:30:00,920 --> 00:30:02,680
Ken means diligence.

622
00:30:03,670 --> 00:30:04,670
My surname is Xue.

623
00:30:04,680 --> 00:30:05,920
Just call me Old Xue.

624
00:30:05,920 --> 00:30:06,880
Mr. Xue.

625
00:30:06,950 --> 00:30:07,500
Thanks.

626
00:30:07,880 --> 00:30:08,600
Take a break.

627
00:30:08,600 --> 00:30:09,270
Okay.

628
00:30:10,590 --> 00:30:11,070
Dad.

629
00:30:11,070 --> 00:30:12,550
Where have you been?

630
00:30:15,800 --> 00:30:16,880
Xiaoyu is at home.

631
00:30:16,900 --> 00:30:17,760
She was hungry.

632
00:30:17,920 --> 00:30:19,680
So I got her something to eat.

633
00:30:20,220 --> 00:30:21,130
It's okay. I'm not leaving.

634
00:30:21,130 --> 00:30:22,460
I'll stay here with you.

635
00:30:22,850 --> 00:30:23,440
Alright.

636
00:30:23,570 --> 00:30:24,480
Get some sleep.

637
00:30:37,140 --> 00:30:38,870
Her lungs are recovering fast.

638
00:30:38,960 --> 00:30:41,820
She can be discharged
after this morning's IV drip.

639
00:30:42,920 --> 00:30:44,510
Take the child home.

640
00:30:45,270 --> 00:30:47,000
Come back if anything happens.

641
00:30:47,960 --> 00:30:48,590
That way,

642
00:30:49,570 --> 00:30:51,360
it can lighten your burden.

643
00:30:52,780 --> 00:30:54,650
Director, I still want to ask about

644
00:30:54,650 --> 00:30:55,980
the kidney transplant.

645
00:30:57,070 --> 00:30:57,750
Roughly when

646
00:30:57,750 --> 00:31:00,270
will it be our turn?

647
00:31:02,010 --> 00:31:03,480
Haven't I explained this to you?

648
00:31:03,480 --> 00:31:04,850
It's not up to the hospital.

649
00:31:04,850 --> 00:31:06,380
I can't say for sure either.

650
00:31:06,510 --> 00:31:07,710
I understand that.

651
00:31:07,990 --> 00:31:08,880
But please understand me.

652
00:31:08,880 --> 00:31:10,920
I don't want to keep bothering you.

653
00:31:11,230 --> 00:31:13,800
But just waiting like this is torture.

654
00:31:14,960 --> 00:31:15,590
I'm also afraid

655
00:31:15,590 --> 00:31:18,240
that some complications might pop up.

656
00:31:18,800 --> 00:31:19,990
Mentally

657
00:31:20,270 --> 00:31:21,160
and financially,

658
00:31:21,160 --> 00:31:22,680
I can't take it anymore.

659
00:31:23,120 --> 00:31:24,780
But without a donated kidney,

660
00:31:24,930 --> 00:31:26,260
I can't speed things up.

661
00:31:27,590 --> 00:31:28,680
Didn't I tell you that

662
00:31:28,680 --> 00:31:30,540
as long as there's a suitable kidney,

663
00:31:30,540 --> 00:31:32,670
scheduling the surgery is easy?

664
00:31:36,440 --> 00:31:37,920
Alright, relax.

665
00:31:38,520 --> 00:31:39,690
Jiajia is already

666
00:31:39,720 --> 00:31:41,460
at the top of our hospital's list.

667
00:31:41,460 --> 00:31:42,430
Many patients

668
00:31:42,950 --> 00:31:45,300
aren't even physically fit for surgery.

669
00:31:52,030 --> 00:31:52,830
I understand.

670
00:32:02,330 --> 00:32:03,000
Mrs. Xue.

671
00:32:04,160 --> 00:32:04,960
You haven't had breakfast, right?

672
00:32:04,960 --> 00:32:06,400
I bought some for you.

673
00:32:07,050 --> 00:32:07,920
I already had breakfast.

674
00:32:07,920 --> 00:32:08,440
No.

675
00:32:08,790 --> 00:32:09,720
We can't accept this.

676
00:32:09,720 --> 00:32:10,200
No, no.

677
00:32:10,200 --> 00:32:10,920
Let me express my gratitude.

678
00:32:10,920 --> 00:32:12,400
Mr. Xue helped me a lot.

679
00:32:12,680 --> 00:32:13,750
It's just a small token.

680
00:32:13,750 --> 00:32:14,480
Thank you.

681
00:32:14,480 --> 00:32:15,740
How are things lately?

682
00:32:15,940 --> 00:32:17,680
Let's check your blood pressure.

683
00:32:17,680 --> 00:32:18,590
Same as always.

684
00:32:20,240 --> 00:32:21,070
It takes time.

685
00:32:21,070 --> 00:32:22,400
You have to take it slow.

686
00:32:23,720 --> 00:32:25,200
Can I see his medical record?

687
00:32:25,200 --> 00:32:27,200
Since Jiajia also has a lung infection,

688
00:32:27,200 --> 00:32:29,310
I want to see what meds he's on.

689
00:32:29,770 --> 00:32:30,480
Here you are.

690
00:32:30,480 --> 00:32:32,080
All of these are his records.

691
00:32:32,200 --> 00:32:32,830
Yeah.

692
00:32:34,450 --> 00:32:35,580
So many medicines.

693
00:32:35,600 --> 00:32:36,070
Yes.

694
00:32:36,100 --> 00:32:37,700
But the two kids' conditions

695
00:32:38,000 --> 00:32:39,000
are definitely different.

696
00:32:39,000 --> 00:32:39,680
Yes.

697
00:32:40,370 --> 00:32:41,310
Go wash up quickly.

698
00:32:41,310 --> 00:32:42,110
It's not crowded now.

699
00:32:42,110 --> 00:32:42,920
Mr. Xue.

700
00:32:43,290 --> 00:32:43,900
Look,

701
00:32:43,930 --> 00:32:45,510
Jiajia's father brought us breakfast.

702
00:32:45,510 --> 00:32:46,030
Thanks.

703
00:32:46,030 --> 00:32:46,480
It's okay.

704
00:32:46,480 --> 00:32:48,080
It's just something simple.

705
00:33:21,720 --> 00:33:22,400
Haven't you left yet?

706
00:33:22,400 --> 00:33:23,460
What are you doing?

707
00:33:29,150 --> 00:33:30,170
Jiajia is amazing.

708
00:33:30,170 --> 00:33:31,510
You are going to leave here.

709
00:33:31,510 --> 00:33:32,180
That's the way.

710
00:33:32,180 --> 00:33:33,240
Go home when you're well.

711
00:33:33,240 --> 00:33:34,830
No need to stay in the hospital
if you're not sick,

712
00:33:34,830 --> 00:33:35,400
right?

713
00:33:37,330 --> 00:33:38,680
I really envy you.

714
00:33:39,880 --> 00:33:41,230
He'll get better in time.

715
00:33:41,230 --> 00:33:41,840
Yes.

716
00:33:42,100 --> 00:33:43,170
My boy will recover soon,

717
00:33:43,170 --> 00:33:43,800
right?

718
00:33:44,960 --> 00:33:45,560
By the way,

719
00:33:46,160 --> 00:33:47,070
I'm going to get some food.

720
00:33:47,070 --> 00:33:48,000
Can you keep an eye on my son for me?

721
00:33:48,000 --> 00:33:48,720
Do you have time?

722
00:33:48,720 --> 00:33:49,720
Yes. We're not leaving yet.

723
00:33:49,720 --> 00:33:51,270
The Director wants to talk to me.

724
00:33:51,270 --> 00:33:51,930
Okay, okay.

725
00:33:52,110 --> 00:33:52,750
I'll come back quickly.

726
00:33:52,750 --> 00:33:53,810
It's fine, no rush.

727
00:33:56,000 --> 00:33:56,880
Jiang.

728
00:33:56,880 --> 00:33:59,000
I come for dialysis every week.

729
00:33:59,090 --> 00:34:00,960
I'll bring you something fun next week.

730
00:34:00,960 --> 00:34:03,270
I have picture books at home.

731
00:34:03,350 --> 00:34:05,000
You can use colored pens

732
00:34:05,000 --> 00:34:07,060
to color the images in picture books.

733
00:34:13,639 --> 00:34:14,900
Do you know how to play?

734
00:34:15,150 --> 00:34:16,550
What is Huarong Path?

735
00:34:18,110 --> 00:34:19,920
I'm not very good at it.

736
00:34:24,070 --> 00:34:25,400
Hello, Uncle Yang.

737
00:34:25,420 --> 00:34:26,130
Jiajia,

738
00:34:26,159 --> 00:34:28,020
eat light meals when you get back.

739
00:34:28,440 --> 00:34:28,880
Okay.

740
00:34:29,250 --> 00:34:30,600
Light meals.

741
00:34:30,840 --> 00:34:32,159
How are you feeling today, handsome?

742
00:34:32,159 --> 00:34:32,830
Put your shoes on.

743
00:34:32,830 --> 00:34:33,290
Come on.

744
00:34:34,330 --> 00:34:35,670
I'm going to draw some blood

745
00:34:35,670 --> 00:34:36,659
for a checkup.

746
00:34:36,679 --> 00:34:37,280
Come here.

747
00:34:38,540 --> 00:34:40,600
Are you scared of blood draws, Jiang?

748
00:34:40,639 --> 00:34:42,330
Actually, a little bit.

749
00:34:42,469 --> 00:34:43,630
A little bit, huh?

750
00:35:02,840 --> 00:35:03,840
Xiaoyu.

751
00:35:05,280 --> 00:35:06,360
Xiaoyu.

752
00:35:08,070 --> 00:35:09,150
Xiaoyu.

753
00:35:11,280 --> 00:35:12,920
What is Xiaoyu doing?

754
00:35:15,150 --> 00:35:15,760
Xiaoyu.

755
00:35:15,760 --> 00:35:17,150
Dad bought me a new puzzle.

756
00:35:17,150 --> 00:35:18,410
Let's put it together.

757
00:35:18,810 --> 00:35:20,870
I will give it to Jiang when it's done.

758
00:35:26,450 --> 00:35:27,080
Look.

759
00:35:27,470 --> 00:35:29,320
This is a blueprint.

760
00:35:34,730 --> 00:35:35,730
Thanks, Xiaoyu.

761
00:35:48,150 --> 00:35:48,750
What's up?

762
00:35:49,360 --> 00:35:50,280
Nie has already

763
00:35:50,280 --> 00:35:52,240
finished Liu Qiang's autopsy report.

764
00:35:52,240 --> 00:35:53,500
It's just as we guessed.

765
00:35:53,500 --> 00:35:55,030
He did take hallucinogens.

766
00:35:55,320 --> 00:35:58,160
And it's a new state-controlled substance.

767
00:35:59,880 --> 00:36:01,840
Didn't the City Bureau say

768
00:36:01,840 --> 00:36:02,840
what Ding Lai bought is

769
00:36:02,840 --> 00:36:04,700
the new drug from the foreign lab?

770
00:36:04,840 --> 00:36:06,370
Now everything matches up.

771
00:36:06,590 --> 00:36:07,110
Okay.

772
00:36:07,360 --> 00:36:07,840
Listen.

773
00:36:07,840 --> 00:36:09,500
Don't report to Director Dai.

774
00:36:09,550 --> 00:36:11,030
Let's go to Liu Qiang's home again
tomorrow

775
00:36:11,030 --> 00:36:13,070
to see if we can find any other clues.

776
00:36:14,710 --> 00:36:16,760
I just finished reporting to Director Dai.

777
00:36:16,760 --> 00:36:18,290
Why are you so quick to talk?

778
00:36:18,670 --> 00:36:19,070
Well,

779
00:36:19,280 --> 00:36:20,440
Director Dai takes this case
very seriously.

780
00:36:20,440 --> 00:36:21,590
He specifically told me

781
00:36:21,590 --> 00:36:23,650
to notify him immediately
if there were any results.

782
00:36:23,650 --> 00:36:24,300
Besides,

783
00:36:24,630 --> 00:36:26,320
why don't you want me to tell him?

784
00:36:26,320 --> 00:36:27,360
When Director Dai is informed,

785
00:36:27,360 --> 00:36:28,770
he'll report it to the City Bureau.

786
00:36:28,770 --> 00:36:30,790
Will we still get to keep this case then?

787
00:36:30,790 --> 00:36:32,020
I think

788
00:36:32,470 --> 00:36:33,320
sometimes we should

789
00:36:33,320 --> 00:36:34,840
stick to the rules.

790
00:36:35,000 --> 00:36:35,880
You're so timid.

791
00:36:35,880 --> 00:36:37,210
What kind of cop are you?

792
00:36:37,230 --> 00:36:38,590
You're not even as brave as my two sons.

793
00:36:38,590 --> 00:36:39,230
Hang up now.

794
00:36:39,230 --> 00:36:40,560
Don't waste my battery.

795
00:36:42,220 --> 00:36:46,820
[Nuanfeng County Public Security
Bureau Committee]

796
00:36:52,230 --> 00:36:53,360
Come on. Right here.

797
00:36:54,880 --> 00:36:56,810
Stop what you're doing, everyone.

798
00:36:59,560 --> 00:37:00,960
Let me introduce you.

799
00:37:01,090 --> 00:37:01,930
This is Officer Jin Longzheng

800
00:37:01,930 --> 00:37:04,930
from the Municipal Narcotics Unit.

801
00:37:05,520 --> 00:37:06,120
Qin,

802
00:37:06,540 --> 00:37:07,870
you two know each other, right?

803
00:37:07,870 --> 00:37:09,800
You've worked on missions together.

804
00:37:09,800 --> 00:37:10,660
That is Tan Jie,

805
00:37:10,960 --> 00:37:11,700
Wang Guangming,

806
00:37:11,700 --> 00:37:12,820
Li and Sun.

807
00:37:13,190 --> 00:37:14,040
The City Bureau

808
00:37:14,040 --> 00:37:15,890
takes this case very seriously.

809
00:37:16,310 --> 00:37:18,260
They hope that through Liu Qiang's case,

810
00:37:18,260 --> 00:37:20,610
we can uncover the drug dens in Nuanhai

811
00:37:21,000 --> 00:37:22,150
and wipe them out in one go.

812
00:37:22,150 --> 00:37:22,710
Then, for this case,

813
00:37:22,710 --> 00:37:23,970
we're counting on you.

814
00:37:24,550 --> 00:37:27,150
I hope that while ensuring your safety,

815
00:37:27,280 --> 00:37:29,610
you can solve the case
as soon as possible.

816
00:37:30,080 --> 00:37:30,710
Just in time.

817
00:37:30,710 --> 00:37:31,610
Are you looking for me, Director Dai?

818
00:37:31,610 --> 00:37:32,780
Let me introduce.

819
00:37:33,110 --> 00:37:33,840
This is Officer Jin Longzheng

820
00:37:33,840 --> 00:37:36,320
from the Municipal Narcotics Unit.

821
00:37:36,840 --> 00:37:37,760
To solve the case quickly,

822
00:37:37,760 --> 00:37:38,880
I specially allocated

823
00:37:38,880 --> 00:37:40,810
other police forces to assist you.

824
00:37:40,880 --> 00:37:43,970
This is Hu Wenjing from
our county Criminal Investigation Team.

825
00:37:43,970 --> 00:37:44,920
She's a veteran detective.

826
00:37:44,920 --> 00:37:47,050
Hope we can have great collaboration.

827
00:37:50,670 --> 00:37:51,230
Come on.

828
00:37:51,530 --> 00:37:52,060
Welcome.

829
00:37:55,320 --> 00:37:56,540
I reviewed Liu Qiang's case.

830
00:37:56,540 --> 00:37:57,810
I want to confirm a few things

831
00:37:57,810 --> 00:37:59,470
and plan to visit his home now.

832
00:38:00,080 --> 00:38:00,520
Okay.

833
00:38:01,150 --> 00:38:01,680
Alright.

834
00:38:02,230 --> 00:38:03,630
We'll go there right now.

835
00:38:05,650 --> 00:38:06,650
Did you hear that?

836
00:38:06,960 --> 00:38:07,810
Qin said

837
00:38:07,840 --> 00:38:09,070
we'll go there right now.

838
00:38:09,070 --> 00:38:10,320
You go and assist them,

839
00:38:10,320 --> 00:38:11,520
showing them the way.

840
00:38:11,800 --> 00:38:13,030
After all, no one is

841
00:38:13,030 --> 00:38:14,030
more familiar with every area

842
00:38:14,030 --> 00:38:15,350
of our county than you,

843
00:38:15,370 --> 00:38:15,960
right?

844
00:38:32,720 --> 00:38:34,880
Liu Qiang lived in Room 201, Unit 2.

845
00:38:35,400 --> 00:38:35,950
Let's go.

846
00:38:36,440 --> 00:38:37,190
Room 201, right?

847
00:38:37,190 --> 00:38:37,630
Yes.

848
00:38:37,750 --> 00:38:39,410
You don't need to come with us.

849
00:38:39,920 --> 00:38:40,550
Why?

850
00:38:40,790 --> 00:38:42,270
This is a narcotics case.

851
00:38:42,290 --> 00:38:43,490
We won't trouble you.

852
00:39:09,630 --> 00:39:10,510
Let me ask you.

853
00:39:10,960 --> 00:39:12,890
You know nothing at all

854
00:39:13,620 --> 00:39:15,310
about your husband Liu Qiang's drug use?

855
00:39:15,310 --> 00:39:16,040
Stop asking.

856
00:39:16,040 --> 00:39:18,450
I don't know anything.

857
00:39:21,200 --> 00:39:22,400
She said

858
00:39:22,420 --> 00:39:23,950
she doesn't know anything.

859
00:39:23,970 --> 00:39:24,840
So you know something about that?

860
00:39:24,840 --> 00:39:25,480
Yes.

861
00:39:25,630 --> 00:39:26,440
Then tell me.

862
00:39:27,310 --> 00:39:28,020
My uncle

863
00:39:29,080 --> 00:39:30,610
committed suicide, right?

864
00:39:30,870 --> 00:39:32,400
How did he become a suspect?

865
00:39:32,800 --> 00:39:33,510
Who did he hurt?

866
00:39:33,510 --> 00:39:34,320
Tell me.

867
00:39:35,520 --> 00:39:36,330
Listen to me.

868
00:39:36,630 --> 00:39:38,550
I am currently questioning
the suspect's family

869
00:39:38,550 --> 00:39:39,940
on site in accordance with the law.

870
00:39:39,940 --> 00:39:41,070
Do not interfere with our investigation.

871
00:39:41,070 --> 00:39:43,440
And you are not
Liu Qiang's immediate family.

872
00:39:43,440 --> 00:39:45,970
I'm asking you to
leave the inquiry scene now,

873
00:39:46,030 --> 00:39:46,550
okay?

874
00:39:46,550 --> 00:39:47,320
This is my uncle's house.

875
00:39:47,320 --> 00:39:48,320
Why should I leave?

876
00:39:48,320 --> 00:39:49,190
Leave.

877
00:39:49,440 --> 00:39:50,590
I'll say it one more time.

878
00:39:50,590 --> 00:39:53,000
I'm asking you to
leave the inquiry scene now.

879
00:39:53,000 --> 00:39:53,920
If you don't follow my order,

880
00:39:53,920 --> 00:39:56,110
I will take coercive measures against you.

881
00:39:56,110 --> 00:39:56,660
Understood?

882
00:39:56,660 --> 00:39:57,510
Coercive measures?

883
00:39:57,510 --> 00:39:58,190
I... I'm telling you.

884
00:39:58,190 --> 00:39:59,070
I doubt your identity.

885
00:39:59,070 --> 00:39:59,670
I'm telling you.

886
00:39:59,670 --> 00:40:01,150
Give me your badge number.

887
00:40:01,150 --> 00:40:01,590
I'll call 110

888
00:40:01,590 --> 00:40:02,320
to verify it.

889
00:40:02,840 --> 00:40:03,700
I have shown you

890
00:40:03,710 --> 00:40:04,280
my ID

891
00:40:04,280 --> 00:40:05,760
and search warrant, haven't I?

892
00:40:05,760 --> 00:40:06,110
Fake.

893
00:40:06,110 --> 00:40:07,320
Couldn't they be fake?

894
00:40:07,320 --> 00:40:08,480
There are so many scammers
and fraudsters nowadays.

895
00:40:08,480 --> 00:40:09,110
You look scruffy.

896
00:40:09,110 --> 00:40:09,800
You don't look like a good person.

897
00:40:09,800 --> 00:40:10,730
I'm telling you.

898
00:40:11,190 --> 00:40:12,480
You're just making trouble.

899
00:40:12,480 --> 00:40:12,880
Jin.

900
00:40:12,880 --> 00:40:13,280
Come here.

901
00:40:13,280 --> 00:40:13,550
What are you doing?

902
00:40:13,550 --> 00:40:14,030
Take him outside.

903
00:40:14,030 --> 00:40:14,840
You want to hit me, right?

904
00:40:14,840 --> 00:40:15,280
Come on.

905
00:40:15,280 --> 00:40:16,140
Don't touch me.

906
00:40:16,230 --> 00:40:17,090
Don't touch me!

907
00:40:18,110 --> 00:40:18,710
Don't touch me!

908
00:40:18,710 --> 00:40:19,510
What's wrong?

909
00:40:21,910 --> 00:40:22,670
Yang Xinyu, come out for a second.

910
00:40:22,670 --> 00:40:23,670
Let me talk to you.

911
00:40:25,840 --> 00:40:26,900
This is the police.

912
00:40:34,630 --> 00:40:36,560
Don't get excited. Just calm down.

913
00:40:39,210 --> 00:40:40,810
My uncle committed suicide.

914
00:40:41,310 --> 00:40:43,310
You came to search as soon as he died.

915
00:40:43,880 --> 00:40:45,180
Can my aunt handle this?

916
00:40:45,180 --> 00:40:47,180
Besides, if the neighbors see this,

917
00:40:47,280 --> 00:40:48,280
they'll think my uncle did something

918
00:40:48,280 --> 00:40:49,070
horrible and unforgivable.

919
00:40:49,070 --> 00:40:50,250
How can my aunt live here?

920
00:40:50,250 --> 00:40:51,080
I understand.

921
00:40:51,760 --> 00:40:53,190
But your uncle used drugs.

922
00:40:53,190 --> 00:40:54,520
It's not a small matter.

923
00:40:55,070 --> 00:40:56,280
We know

924
00:40:56,280 --> 00:40:57,380
what kind of person your uncle was.

925
00:40:57,380 --> 00:40:58,260
Like my dad,

926
00:40:58,290 --> 00:41:00,020
he was just an ordinary worker.

927
00:41:00,150 --> 00:41:01,880
So who pushed him down this path?

928
00:41:01,880 --> 00:41:02,900
Don't we need to find that out?

929
00:41:02,900 --> 00:41:05,370
Only then can we
give your aunt an explanation.

930
00:41:05,370 --> 00:41:06,410
I get that.

931
00:41:06,880 --> 00:41:09,830
The point is that
this police officer has a bad attitude.

932
00:41:09,830 --> 00:41:11,750
He was just following procedure.

933
00:41:12,380 --> 00:41:13,000
Who knows

934
00:41:13,000 --> 00:41:14,510
whether he just used drugs himself,

935
00:41:14,510 --> 00:41:15,840
or he also sold drugs?

936
00:41:15,840 --> 00:41:17,240
We can't say for sure yet.

937
00:41:17,290 --> 00:41:18,140
Selling drugs?

938
00:41:18,140 --> 00:41:18,980
Could he do that?

939
00:41:18,980 --> 00:41:19,490
No way.

940
00:41:19,850 --> 00:41:21,110
Is that even possible?

941
00:41:21,110 --> 00:41:21,760
Whether it's possible or not,

942
00:41:21,760 --> 00:41:22,710
we have to investigate thoroughly

943
00:41:22,710 --> 00:41:23,960
to clear his name.

944
00:41:23,960 --> 00:41:24,480
Right?

945
00:41:26,920 --> 00:41:27,960
Think it over carefully.

946
00:41:27,960 --> 00:41:28,960
See if you can remember

947
00:41:28,960 --> 00:41:29,880
any valuable information

948
00:41:29,880 --> 00:41:30,630
and tell us.

949
00:41:30,800 --> 00:41:33,660
It's better for everyone
if we solve this case soon.

950
00:41:36,720 --> 00:41:37,280
My uncle

951
00:41:37,280 --> 00:41:38,760
didn't drink.

952
00:41:39,480 --> 00:41:40,210
But recently,

953
00:41:40,210 --> 00:41:41,010
he went to a bar

954
00:41:41,710 --> 00:41:42,950
frequently.

955
00:41:43,660 --> 00:41:44,430
What bar?

956
00:41:48,830 --> 00:41:56,480
[Next Episode Preview]
